If Barrick Gold really wanted a public and transparent debate, he could do so by following the scientific norms used by the authors of Noir Canada.
You have a right of reply.
The university world, to which we belong, has long been able to manage debates and disagreements and resolve conflicts.
Barrick Gold’s unreasonable persecution clearly shows that, contrary to what it claims, it has no desire to make a transparent debate.
It is a loss for the university world, but also for the public debate in Canada, and it is time for governments to put in place devices that limit this kind of abusive persecution.
