As the first sign of the party’s restructuring, Vice President Horst Seehofer, Federal Minister of Agriculture, one of Huber’s prospective successors, also holds a position in the small intelligence group that begins negotiations with the liberal FDP and the right-wing Free Electors about a possible government coalition in Munich.
